Chapter 7: Self‑Diagnostics — Recursive Self‑Modeling (Axiom 6)

7.1 Self‑Model Architecture

Self‑model $\mathcal{M}_{\text{self}}$ (lightweight capsule network) predicts nucleus outputs $\hat{y}_k(t)$ from raw sensor data. It updates at 1 Hz, weights at 0.01 Hz.

7.2 Divergence Monitoring

Define $\delta_k(t) = \|y_k(t) - \hat{y}_k(t)\|_2$. Threshold $\epsilon_k = 3\sigma_k$ with $\sigma_k$ nominal standard deviation.

Assumption 7.1 (Markov Approximation): The divergence sequence $\{\delta_k(t)\}$ can be modeled as a stationary ergodic Markov chain over a finite set of levels (e.g., “normal”, “mild”, “high”). This is justified by the fact that capsule dynamics and task distribution are mixing; the spectral gap can be estimated from simulations.

7.3 Graduated Response Protocol

· Level 1: $\epsilon_k < \delta_k < 2\epsilon_k$ for $T_{\text{alert}}=10$ steps → increase sampling rate, flag low confidence.
· Level 2: $2\epsilon_k \le \delta_k < 3\epsilon_k$ for $10$ steps → suspend nucleus, redistribute function via Hamiltonian coupling.
· Level 3: $\delta_k \ge 3\epsilon_k$ for $10$ steps → halt, request human intervention.

Proposition 7.1 (False‑Alarm Bound via Spectral Gap):
Let $\rho = \sup_x P(\delta_k \ge \epsilon_k \mid \text{state } x)$ be the maximum one‑step exceedance probability. Let $\lambda$ be the second largest eigenvalue in magnitude of the transition matrix restricted to the set of states where exceedance is possible. Then

\mathbb{P}(\text{Level 3 false alarm}) \le \rho \cdot \lambda^{T_{\text{alert}}-1}.

For the E4 architecture, $\rho \le 1/9$ by Chebyshev’s inequality, and $\lambda$ can be made < 1 due to geometric ergodicity. For a mixing time $t_{\text{mix}}$, we have $\lambda \approx 1 - 1/t_{\text{mix}}$, giving an exponentially decaying bound.

Proof: The probability of a run of $T_{\text{alert}}$ consecutive exceedances is at most the probability of entering an exceedance state times the probability of staying there for $T_{\text{alert}}-1$ steps. The latter is bounded by the spectral radius of the sub‑transition matrix on the exceedance set, which is $\lambda$ [7]. $\blacksquare$

Proposition 7.2 (Axiom 6 Satisfaction): The self‑model, divergence monitor, and response protocol constitute meta‑recursive regulation, satisfying FCI Axiom 6 by construction.

