C.2 Computation of Critical Coupling Strength \gamma_c

For Gaussian beliefs, U_k(q_k) = \frac12 (q_k - \mu_k)^T \Sigma_k^{-1} (q_k - \mu_k), so \nabla^2 U_k = \Sigma_k^{-1}. With \|\Sigma_k\|_2 \approx 0.1, \lambda_{\min}(\nabla^2 U_k) \approx 10. The Hessian of the Jensen‑Shannon divergence between two Gaussians is \nabla^2_{12} D_{\text{JS}} = \frac12 (\Sigma_1^{-1} + \Sigma_2^{-1}), so \|\nabla^2_{12} \Phi\|_2 \le \frac12 (\|\Sigma_1^{-1}\|_2 + \|\Sigma_2^{-1}\|_2) \approx 10. Thus \gamma_c \approx 10/10 = 1. To ensure a safety margin, we set \gamma = 0.5.

